snippets.title: CatalogService getEntry Sample
snippets.description: Gets an Entry. **Caution**: The BigQuery metadata that is stored in Dataplex Catalog is changing. For more information, see [Changes to BigQuery metadata stored in Dataplex Catalog](https://cloud.google.com/dataplex/docs/biqquery-metadata-changes).

snippets.title: CatalogService lookupEntry Sample
snippets.description: Looks up a single Entry by name using the permission on the source system. **Caution**: The BigQuery metadata that is stored in Dataplex Catalog is changing. For more information, see [Changes to BigQuery metadata stored in Dataplex Catalog](https://cloud.google.com/dataplex/docs/biqquery-metadata-changes).

snippets.title: CatalogService searchEntries Sample
snippets.description: Searches for Entries matching the given query and scope.

snippets.title: CatalogService createMetadataJob Sample
snippets.description: Creates a metadata job. For example, use a metadata job to import Dataplex Catalog entries and aspects from a third-party system into Dataplex.

snippets.title: CatalogService cancelMetadataJob Sample
snippets.description: Cancels a metadata job. If you cancel a metadata import job that is in progress, the changes in the job might be partially applied. We recommend that you reset the state of the entry groups in your project by running another metadata job that reverts the changes from the canceled job.

snippets.title: CatalogService updateContent Sample
snippets.description: Update a content. Only supports full resource update.

snippets.title: CatalogService getIamPolicy Sample
snippets.description: Gets the access control policy for a contentitem resource. A `NOT_FOUND` error is returned if the resource does not exist. An empty policy is returned if the resource exists but does not have a policy set on it. Caller must have Google IAM `dataplex.content.getIamPolicy` permission on the resource.

snippets.title: CatalogService setIamPolicy Sample
snippets.description: Sets the access control policy on the specified contentitem resource. Replaces any existing policy. Caller must have Google IAM `dataplex.content.setIamPolicy` permission on the resource.

snippets.title: CatalogService testIamPermissions Sample
snippets.description: Returns the caller's permissions on a resource. If the resource does not exist, an empty set of permissions is returned (a `NOT_FOUND` error is not returned). A caller is not required to have Google IAM permission to make this request. Note: This operation is designed to be used for building permission-aware UIs and command-line tools, not for authorization checking. This operation may "fail open" without warning.
